		<table width=80% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td class=title>
	Forums Closing? ~ Forums ~ 02-02-2004</td></tr>
	<tr><td class=border>I sent an email out yesterday that said forums would be closing indefinitely. Some of you got this email, but some were returned as undeliverable. Here is a copy of the email.<br><br>--------<br><br>I regret to inform you that I will be closing down forum hosting in the very<br>near future.<br>As you know, the forums have been provided free of charge, without banners<br>or ads for quite some time, which isn't very cost effective for me. So, I<br>have decided to close them down instead of paying even more out of my pocket<br>each month.<br><br>Forum admins will be provided with the entire forum zipped up to do with as<br>they wish. You can find a conversion tool for phpbb on their site<br>www.phpbb.com if your host is php and mysql enabled. I'll do what I can to<br>help, if you need help getting the forum set up on your host.<br><br>If you have any questions feel free to contact me.<br><br>-Grim<br><br>--------<br><br>There is one alternative. I've never asked for donations or requested them before. But some of you would like to keep your forum here instead of dealing with the hassle of moving it. <br><br>I can't tell you how much to donate, but I can tell you that 1 Gig per month costs me about $2.00. The most active forum I am hosting is pushing 6 Gigs a month currently.<br><br>Let me know if you would be interested in donating to keep your forum here and hopefully we can work something out. I would probably set up donations through Paypal.<br><br></td></tr></table><br><br>
